{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017QufBvrpWRgDsRgSN3RAR8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: query-layer-discipline\n     3→description: Keep reads in selectors/querysets and keep write logic in services without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Query Layer Discipline (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when introducing new read patterns.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `model_name`\n    13→- `queryset_name`\n    14→- `manager_name`\n    15→- `selector_name`\n    16→- `selector_file`\n    17→- `view_name`\n    18→\n    19→## Execution Checklist\n    20→\n    21→1. Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet.\n    22→2. Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager.\n    23→3. Define selector entrypoints for query composition.\n    24→4. Update views to consume selectors for reads.\n    25→5. Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code.\n    26→\n    27→## Guardrails\n    28→\n    29→- Avoid query logic scattered in views.\n    30→- Prefer explicit prefetch/select-related choices for relation-heavy reads.\n    31→- Keep selector naming stable and action-oriented.\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5ac6800-962f-49fd-ba1d-4005baf7dfc8","uuid":"7a453663-8339-4fbb-8e62-91d648a63e69"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CKQoXMKpRiVu46D34pvM2g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file is benign — just a checklist document.\n\nApplying the **query-layer-discipline** checklist to your variables:\n\n**1. Chainable read helpers on `EntityQuerySet`**\n- Add methods like `.active()`, `.with_related()` on `EntityQuerySet` so they return `self.filter(...)` and compose.\n\n**2. Expose via `EntityManager`**\n- `objects = EntityManager.from_queryset(EntityQuerySet)()` on `Entity`, so `Entity.objects.active()` works.\n\n**3. Selector entrypoint `select_active_entities`**\n- In `selectors.py`, define `select_active_entities(*, ...) -> EntityQuerySet` that composes queryset helpers (e.g. `Entity.objects.active().with_related()`) and applies explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`.\n\n**4. View `entity_list` consumes the selector**\n- `entity_list` calls `select_active_entities(...)` only — no `Entity.objects.filter(...)` inline, no ad-hoc joins.\n\n**5. Writes stay in services**\n- Any create/update/delete/transaction logic for `Entity` remains in service-layer functions, not in `selectors.py`, not in `entity_list`, not on the queryset/manager.\n\n**Guardrail checks for this run**\n- No query logic in `entity_list` beyond calling `select_active_entities`.\n- `select_active_entities` declares prefetch/select_related explicitly for relation-heavy reads.\n- Selector name is stable and action-oriented (`select_active_entities` — good).\n\nNo files were modified; per CLAUDE.md I'm not running `jig` and not creating files unless required. Let me know which file(s) you want the edits applied to and I'll make the changes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":644,"cache_read_input_tokens":21757,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":644,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":590,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5ac6800-962f-49fd-ba1d-4005baf7dfc8","uuid":"6ca44c2a-7fdb-4f39-9f8d-00d334e199d6"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":15861,"duration_api_ms":15776,"num_turns":6,"result":"The skill file is benign — just a checklist document.\n\nApplying the **query-layer-discipline** checklist to your variables:\n\n**1. Chainable read helpers on `EntityQuerySet`**\n- Add methods like `.active()`, `.with_related()` on `EntityQuerySet` so they return `self.filter(...)` and compose.\n\n**2. Expose via `EntityManager`**\n- `objects = EntityManager.from_queryset(EntityQuerySet)()` on `Entity`, so `Entity.objects.active()` works.\n\n**3. Selector entrypoint `select_active_entities`**\n- In `selectors.py`, define `select_active_entities(*, ...) -> EntityQuerySet` that composes queryset helpers (e.g. `Entity.objects.active().with_related()`) and applies explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`.\n\n**4. View `entity_list` consumes the selector**\n- `entity_list` calls `select_active_entities(...)` only — no `Entity.objects.filter(...)` inline, no ad-hoc joins.\n\n**5. Writes stay in services**\n- Any create/update/delete/transaction logic for `Entity` remains in service-layer functions, not in `selectors.py`, not in `entity_list`, not on the queryset/manager.\n\n**Guardrail checks for this run**\n- No query logic in `entity_list` beyond calling `select_active_entities`.\n- `select_active_entities` declares prefetch/select_related explicitly for relation-heavy reads.\n- Selector name is stable and action-oriented (`select_active_entities` — good).\n\nNo files were modified; per CLAUDE.md I'm not running `jig` and not creating files unless required. Let me know which file(s) you want the edits applied to and I'll make the changes.","session_id":"c5ac6800-962f-49fd-ba1d-4005baf7dfc8","total_cost_usd":0.2764515,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6556,"cache_read_input_tokens":58821,"output_tokens":869,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"